description:
Available to a UFV student who will be completing a minimum of 18 credits in the current academic year (September through April) with a GPA of 3.0 or higher who plans to continue studying at UFV and has demonstrated commitment to leadership with preference in the following order:
1.  Leadership through UFV clubs and associations on campus;
2.  Student who demonstrates leadership off campus (volunteerism of time is not the only factor.  Student must demonstrate characteristics of taking charge and leading in a project, club, and/or association.)

Available to:  A UFV student that meets the following criteria:
 - Demonstrates genuine financial need;
 - First consideration will be given to students who have exhausted all other types of funding (i.e. government programs).  Students who have not accessed government funding will have bursaries awarded based on availability of funds;
 - Enrolled in a UFV Program at a post-secondary level;
 - Show satisfactory academic achievement (2.0 GPA or better).
